* Enum value names (avoiding collisions)

Solution 1, prepend the type name in front of the enum value name:

	package githubql

	// ReactionContent represents emojis that can be attached to Issues, Pull Requests and Comments.
	type ReactionContent string

	// Emojis that can be attached to Issues, Pull Requests and Comments.
	const (
	-	ThumbsUp   ReactionContent = "THUMBS_UP"   // Represents the üëç emoji.
	-	ThumbsDown ReactionContent = "THUMBS_DOWN" // Represents the üëé emoji.
	-	Laugh      ReactionContent = "LAUGH"       // Represents the üòÑ emoji.
	+	ReactionContentThumbsUp   ReactionContent = "THUMBS_UP"   // Represents the üëç emoji.
	+	ReactionContentThumbsDown ReactionContent = "THUMBS_DOWN" // Represents the üëé emoji.
	+	ReactionContentLaugh      ReactionContent = "LAUGH"       // Represents the üòÑ emoji.
	)

Verbose.

* Enum value names (avoiding collisions)

Solution 2, separate by middot-like character €∞ (U+06F0).

	package githubql

	// ReactionContent represents emojis that can be attached to Issues, Pull Requests and Comments.
	type ReactionContent string

	// Emojis that can be attached to Issues, Pull Requests and Comments.
	const (
	-	ThumbsUp   ReactionContent = "THUMBS_UP"   // Represents the üëç emoji.
	-	ThumbsDown ReactionContent = "THUMBS_DOWN" // Represents the üëé emoji.
	-	Laugh      ReactionContent = "LAUGH"       // Represents the üòÑ emoji.
	+	ReactionContent€∞ThumbsUp   ReactionContent = "THUMBS_UP"   // Represents the üëç emoji.
	+	ReactionContent€∞ThumbsDown ReactionContent = "THUMBS_DOWN" // Represents the üëé emoji.
	+	ReactionContent€∞Laugh      ReactionContent = "LAUGH"       // Represents the üòÑ emoji.
	)

Can't be easily typed without autocomplete.

* Enum value names (avoiding collisions)

Solution 3, use shorter initialisms:

	package githubql

	// ReactionContent represents emojis that can be attached to Issues, Pull Requests and Comments.
	type ReactionContent string

	// Emojis that can be attached to Issues, Pull Requests and Comments.
	const (
	-	ThumbsUp   ReactionContent = "THUMBS_UP"   // Represents the üëç emoji.
	-	ThumbsDown ReactionContent = "THUMBS_DOWN" // Represents the üëé emoji.
	-	Laugh      ReactionContent = "LAUGH"       // Represents the üòÑ emoji.
	+	RCThumbsUp   ReactionContent = "THUMBS_UP"   // Represents the üëç emoji.
	+	RCThumbsDown ReactionContent = "THUMBS_DOWN" // Represents the üëé emoji.
	+	RCLaugh      ReactionContent = "LAUGH"       // Represents the üòÑ emoji.
	)

Can still have collisions!

* Enum value names (avoiding collisions)

Solution 4, enum values in separate packages:

	package githubql

	// ReactionContent represents emojis that can be attached to Issues, Pull Requests and Comments.
	type ReactionContent string

: ---

	// Package reactioncontent contains enum values of githubql.ReactionContent type.
	package reactioncontent

	import "github.com/shurcooL/githubql"

	// Emojis that can be attached to Issues, Pull Requests and Comments.
	const (
		ThumbsUp   githubql.ReactionContent = "THUMBS_UP"   // Represents the üëç emoji.
		ThumbsDown githubql.ReactionContent = "THUMBS_DOWN" // Represents the üëé emoji.
		Laugh      githubql.ReactionContent = "LAUGH"       // Represents the üòÑ emoji.
	)

Docs split up; more small packages; import cycle if used in main package.

